                        ANGULAR
Basic Building Blocks Component

1) Module- to import 3rd party modules (root module- app.module.ts)
2) Component - To craete html,css and ts files


Basic Commands

1) To create new project - ng new project_name
2) To create new Component- ng g c component_name
3) to run anugalr files-  ng serve --open

Basic concepts

Data binding - share data between components

ts-> component
html-> view

1)one way data binding - data sharing only one direction
    1.1) component to view (ts->html)
        a) string interpolation- {{expression}}
        b) property binding- [attribute_name]="property"
    
    1.2)View to component(html->ts)

        a) Event binding - (event_name)="function_name()"
        b) Event binding using  $event - (event_name)="function_name()$event"
        c) Event binding using template referencing variable - #variable_name


2) two way data binding

data sharing in both direction(ts->html, html->ts)

    i) ngmodel binding - import formsModule in app.module.ts
    [(ngModel)]="property_name"


    Angular Routing

    To set path for component

    {
        path;value,component:component_name
    },


    login
    {
        path:'',component:LoginComponent
    },


3)Angular services

to hold redundant data

To create new service ng g s service_name


4)Dependency injection

To share data between two dependent classes

constructor(private ds:DataService)

5) Angular directives-
    To manipulate DOM

    a)Component directives(array)

    b)Structural directives(table)
        i) *ngFor
        ii)ngIf



    6)Angular forms

        a)template driven froms(first design html template)
        b)Model driven froms(first design model ts file)
            1)reactive forms
            formGroup,array,control
            for advanced validation

7) Local storage
-setItem - to store data in local storage
-getItem - To get data from ,ocal storage
- removeItem - To remove data from local storage



8) parent child communication

     parent-> child communucation
     child -> parent communication

     eg:
     dashboard ->
     delete -> child

9) Angular pipes









